   <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly:  "Letter of Aristeas, Fictitious report in the form of an epistolary novel
      by the pagan official A. on the circumstances leading to the translation into Greek of the  Pentateuch.
      Written in good  koine by an Alexandrian Jew towards the end of the 2nd cent. BC, A. defends the validity of the Torah, 
      provides allegorical interpretations of the ritual laws, and emphasizes the reliability of the  Septuagint...."
